  "text": "For western blotting, cells were lysed in 20 mM Tris-HCl (pH 7.4), 1 mM EGTA/EDTA, 1% Triton X-100, 1 mM Na 3 VO 4 , 10% glycerol, 1 lgÁmL À1 leupeptin and 1 lgÁmL À1 aprotinin. After centrifugation, cell lysates were subjected to SDS/PAGE and transferred to nitrocellulose membranes, which were then incubated with indicated primary antibodies and IRDye-conjugated secondary antibodies. Protein bands were visualized using an infrared image analyzer (Li-COR Biosciences) [CITATION_1] .",
